November 27, 2021

This README is utilized to start a django project after installing the django framework. The following instructions should be issued from a shell:

# Create a python virtual environment to run the scripts found on the same level as the
# project directory
python3 -m venv venv

# Acivate the python environment
source venv/bin/activate 

# Install django if not installed already
pip install django

# Then we change directories to Hello_prj
cd Hello_prj 

# Run the command to remove warnings, but this is optional
python3 manage.py migrate

# Run the server in a terminal
python3 manage.py runserver

# In a browser, the webpage may be accessed by typing localhost:8000 in the url.
# To view the JSON Hello World, type localhost:8000/hello in the url
# To view the optional template view type localhost:8000/helloTemplate in the url
 
